analysisPopulations.name: All Enrolled Set
analysisPopulations.text: The All Enrolled Set includes all subjects who have signed informed consent and are assigned subject numbers.
analysisPopulations.label: All Enrolled
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The All Enrolled Set includes all subjects who have signed informed consent and are assigned subject numbers.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Signed informed consent AND assigned subject number

analysisPopulations.name: Randomized Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Randomized Set will consist of all randomized subjects. Subjects are considered randomized when they have been deemed eligible for randomization by the investigator and given a randomization number. Subjects who were randomized but did not receive any study treatment at baseline and discontinued study per subject decision will be classified as screen failures.
analysisPopulations.label: Randomized
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Randomized Set will consist of all randomized subjects. Subjects are considered randomized when they have been deemed eligible for randomization by the investigator and given a randomization number. Subjects who were randomized but did not receive any study treatment at baseline and discontinued study per subject decision will be classified as screen failures.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Deemed eligible AND assigned randomization number

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) comprises all randomized subjects who receive at least one study treatment. Subjects in the FAS will be analyzed according to the treatment assigned to them at randomization.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) comprises all randomized subjects who receive at least one study treatment. Subjects in the FAS will be analyzed according to the treatment assigned to them at randomization.

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Safety Analysis Set (SAF) includes all subjects who receive at least one study treatment. Subjects in the SAF will be analyzed according to the actual study treatment they received, where treatment received is defined as the randomized/assigned treatment if the subject took at least one dose of that treatment, or the first treatment received if the randomized/assigned treatment was never received.
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Safety Analysis Set (SAF) includes all subjects who receive at least one study treatment. Subjects in the SAF will be analyzed according to the actual study treatment they received, where treatment received is defined as the randomized/assigned treatment if the subject took at least one dose of that treatment, or the first treatment received if the randomized/assigned treatment was never received.

analysisPopulations.name: Per Protocol Set
analysisPopulations.text: PPS is a subset of the FAS and will exclude or censor data from subjects with important protocol deviations (PDs) and analysis restrictions (ARs) that are expected to majorly affect the validity of the assessment of efficacy at Week 54.
analysisPopulations.label: PPS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: PPS is a subset of the FAS and will exclude or censor data from subjects with important protocol deviations (PDs) and analysis restrictions (ARs) that are expected to majorly affect the validity of the assessment of efficacy at Week 54.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Subset of FAS AND no important protocol deviations/analysis restrictions affecting efficacy validity

characteristics.name: Baseline BCVA
characteristics.description: Best corrected visual acuity categories (<=75, >75 letters)

characteristics.name: Baseline DR severity
characteristics.description: NPDR, Mild or moderate PDR, High-risk PDR or worse, Ungradable as assessed by CRC

characteristics.name: Region
characteristics.description: US and Canada, East Asia, Other

characteristics.name: Prior anti-VEGF treatment
characteristics.description: Prior anti-VEGF treatment in the study eye (yes, no)

characteristics.name: Baseline CSFT
characteristics.description: Central subfield thickness (<280, >=280 um) as assessed by CRC
